===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Argo had a population of 44 people, with 14 households and 8 families residing in the community.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A02665&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 96.4 inhabitants per square mile (37.2/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 19 housing units at an average density of 41.6 per square mile (16.1/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP"/> All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A02665&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

The median age was 44.3 years. 27.3% of residents were under the age of 18 and 22.7% were 65 years of age or older. By broader age groups, 27.3% were under 20, 0.0% were from 20 to 24, 29.5% were from 25 to 44, and 20.5% were from 45 to 64. The gender makeup of the community was 31.8% male and 68.2% female. For every 100 females there were 46.7 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 33.3 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of the 14 households, 35.7% had children under the age of 18 living in them. Of all households, 57.1% were [[Marriage|married-couple households]], 7.1% were cohabiting-couple households, 28.6% were households with a male householder and no spouse or partner present, and 7.1% were households with a female householder and no spouse or partner present. About 42.9% of households were non-families, 35.7% were made up of individuals, and 7.1% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of the 19 housing units, 26.3% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

